.TH XTGEOIP 1 "" "xtgeoip 2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xtgeoip
	Build and manage xt_geoip data from MaxMind GeoLite2 CSVs.

.SH BUILD
Build xt_geoip data from the local CSV copy.
.TP
xtgeoip build
build using local copy of database
.TP
xtgeoip build -l
build using local copy of database in legacy mode
.TP
xtgeoip build -b -p
backup, prune backups, then build
.TP
xtgeoip build -p
unsupported option, build has no prune function
.TP
xtgeoip build -c -f
clean using manifest, then build using local copy of database
.TP
xtgeoip build -b -c -p
backup, prune backups, clean, then build
.TP
xtgeoip build -b -c -p -f
unsupported option, ambiguous and prune does not support force
.SH CONF
Configuration operations.
Usage: xtgeoip conf <FLAG>
.TP
xtgeoip conf
missing required argument, conf requires FLAG
.TP
xtgeoip conf -s
show current config
.TP
xtgeoip conf -d
show default config
.TP
xtgeoip conf -e
edit config
.SH FETCH
Download or refresh the local MaxMind CSV archive set.
.TP
xtgeoip fetch
fetch CSVs
.TP
xtgeoip fetch -p
fetch CSVs, then prune CSVs
.TP
xtgeoip fetch -l
unsupported option, -l is not valid for fetch
.TP
xtgeoip fetch -b
unsupported option, -b is not valid for fetch
.SH RUN
Fetch, then build, optionally wrapping with backup/clean/prune.
.TP
xtgeoip run
fetch, then build
.TP
xtgeoip run -l
fetch, then build in legacy mode
.TP
xtgeoip run -p
fetch, then prune CSVs, then build
.TP
xtgeoip run -c -p
clean using manifest, then fetch, then prune CSVs, then build
.TP
xtgeoip run -c -f
force clean without manifest, then fetch, then build
.TP
xtgeoip run -c -p -f
unsupported option, ambiguous and prune does not support force
.TP
xtgeoip run -b -c -p
unsupported option, ambiguous (does prune apply to fetch or backup?)
.SH VERSION
Show the program version.
.TP
xtgeoip -V
display version
